ered in the later sections. I'm checking whether any class names are missing from the hints...\n\nlooking at s4, I notice `nablarch.common.code.BasicCode` should be included since it's part of the class definitions, though the short name `BasicCode` is already there.\n\nFor s5 and s6, I'm verifying the hints against the table properties—the Japanese terms and their corresponding column names are all accounted for, though the s6 check appears to be cut off.\n\nLooking at s7, I see `NAME_WITH_VALUE` and `SHORT_NAME` are present. For s8, the hints cover the gender classification codes and batch processing states adequately.\n\nThe key issue I'm finding is that `nablarch.common.code.BasicCode` is missing from the s4 hints—a minor V4 compatibility gap. The section count warning about 13 being below 20 isn't really a problem given the appropriate consolidation, and the \"要求 > 実装済み\" section is more of a summary that duplicates the detailed sections, so it's fine to leave it out.\n\nI'm also verifying that the reference to `:ref:`code_manager_validation`` in s1 is correctly included in the knowledge file. Now I'm checking the footnote about pattern table definitions more carefully—the source explains that pattern column names are arbitrary and projects can define as many patterns as needed, but the knowledge file in s5 seems to cut off mid-explanation. コード名称テーブルの定義について、複数のオプション名称を1つのコード値に対して持たせることができ、その数とカラム名は自由に設定できるという点が確認できた。\n\n分析がほぼ完了したので、見つかった問題をまとめると、V4では`nablarch.common.code.BasicCode`の完全修飾名が不足している軽微な問題がある。V3のセクション数については、ソースの見出し数より少ないが、適切にマージされているため問題ではない。ただし、セクション数の検証ルールをもう一度確認する必要がある。RST形式のh2レベルの見出しを数えるという仕様なので、その基準に照らし合わせて再検討してみよう。 The h2 heading count is actually fine—there are 9 h2 headings in the source versus 13 sections in the knowledge file, so the pre-check warning about 20 headings is counting all levels, not just h2. The V3 validation specifically looks at h2 only, so there's no structural issue here.\n\nLooking back through the findings, the main thing